text: You take a moment to stretch out in a warm patch of sunlight, enjoying a brief respite from your warrior duties.
Tempestswirl is talking about a kittypet she met on patrol. You recall that kittypet as well. Small world!

Fresh-kill tastes a little better, a little brighter, like it's cleaner. While the Clan might be a little thinner than they used to be, it seems as if they can now eat anything they catch again - if they can catch it!

Lorestar goes on and on about what a great alliance LoreClan and SilentClan have during their speech at the Gathering. SilentClan's leader coughs meaningfully; during their speech, they announce SilentClan will be focusing on its own priorities in the coming moons and suggest LoreClan does the same. (SilentClan relations worsened.)
Electricnight draws a pretty symbol in the sand that Lightningdapple makes sure not to mess up. (low positive effect)
Willowbreeze thinks Vulturethorn isn't very considerate of others. (low negative effect)
Lorestar spends some time sheltering with Sunpaw during a storm. (medium positive effect)
Lightningdapple points out that maybe Lorestar's jealousy over Bronzepaw is caused by insecurity and envy rather than genuine hate. It gives Lorestar a lot to think about. (positive effect)
When Lorestar tells Wrenrush about a goal they have, Wrenrush snickers at it. (low negative effect)
Steadyheart tells her Clanmates that something's off about Goldenblink. (medium negative effect)
Goldenblink thanked Yellowfang for bringing her food. (low positive effect)
Yellowfang, Slightdust, and Steadyheart had a nice talk while eating. (neutral effect)
Yellowfang sees a pretty flower in Squirrelpaw's nest. (low positive effect)
Yellowfang purrs for a long time at one of Lorestar's lame jokes. (high positive effect)
Slateflood calls out the Clan for targeting Rootpounce. (high positive effect)
Serpentgleam yawns while Dreamdawn is trying to tell him something. (low negative effect)
Dreamdawn nods politely as Emberdrift passes by. (neutral effect)
Nightmaredusk is glaring daggers at Electricnight. (medium negative effect)
Nightmaredusk, wanting to help keep her Clanmates in shape and ready for anything, woke Heatherdaisy, Darkspark, Ferretslither, and Leopardbreeze up early for morning stretches. (negative effect)
Emberdrift eats with Serpentgleam all the time! (high positive effect)
Rootpounce is poised to help train Leopardbreeze. (medium positive effect)
Leopardbreeze doubts whether Tempestswirl even likes her at all... (high negative effect)
Tsunamiroar and Rootpounce heckled another Clan at the Gathering together. (high positive effect)
Serpentgleam bluntly claims Tsunamiroar is being childish over his relationship with Slateflood. (positive effect)
Tsunamiroar sees Lorestar be kind to one of Tsunamiroar's friends. (low positive effect)
Murmurfox didn't put a lot of thought into an answer for Galeswift's question. (low negative effect)
Goldenblink finds more comfort in the wasteland of the Dark Forest than the supposed paradise of StarClan. (Dark Forest faith increased)
Goldenblink and Lorestar roll up moss balls together. (low positive effect)
Goldenblink watches Raingrass wind up for a sneeze, but it never happens. (neutral effect)
While her Clanmates pray to StarClan, Ferretslither gives thanks to a force much darker. (Dark Forest faith increased)
Ferretslither complains about something Lorestar did. (low negative effect)
Ferretslither sees Serpentgleam being gentle with an injured bug. (low positive effect)
Darkspark offers to groom a hard-to-reach place for Bronzepaw, who thanks her earnestly. (high positive effect)
Darkspark shares a joke about a neighboring Clan with Bronzepaw. (low positive effect)
Both Heatherdaisy and Galeswift enthusiastically congratulate another Clanmate on something. (high positive effect)
Emberdrift helps Heatherdaisy get a thorn out of his paw. (low positive effect)
Buggs swears that Squirrelpaw's fangs are longer than usual. (medium negative effect)
Buggs sees that Lightningdapple's piece of prey looks tastier and asks if she'd like to swap. She agrees happily, saying she likes that one better. (high positive effect)
Murmurfox eats a meal without thanking StarClan. (StarClan faith decreased)
Murmurfox settles near Slateflood to eat her fresh-kill. (medium positive effect)
Spiritmeadow asks Lightningdapple a bold question. (neutral effect)
The leader was more impressed by what Serpentgleam brought back from a hunting patrol than what Tempestswirl did. (medium negative effect)
Snowyfoot and Willowbreeze always challenge one another. (high positive effect)
Snowyfoot snickers as Nightmaredusk falls flat on her face in the middle of camp. (medium negative effect)
Hazeltalon is telling Wrenrush something interesting about another Clan. (medium positive effect)
Hazeltalon notices that Tempestswirl makes other Clanmates laugh more than he does. (medium negative effect)
Wrenrush and Vulturethorn have an argument about who should get a pretty feather, and end up destroying it in their fight. (low negative effect)
Emeraldcall trips over air in the middle of camp, cursing StarClan in embarrassment. (StarClan faith increased)
Emeraldcall has drawn the ire of Yellowfang by deliberately taking the last of her favorite nesting materials for himself. (low negative effect)
Lightningdapple bluntly claims Emeraldcall is being childish over his relationship with Tsunamiroar. (positive effect)
Bronzepaw has excelled at every task placed before him. Despite his young age, he is more than ready to be a warrior. He is given the name Bronzecrag, honoring his hard work.
Bronzecrag doesn't think that Emeraldcall has been completely honest lately. (low negative effect)
Squirrelpaw and Snowyfoot notice a cloud is shaped like a bird. (neutral effect)
Electricnight remembers something nice that Wrenrush did. (low positive effect)
Electricnight points out a constellation to Lightningdapple. (neutral effect)
Electricnight and Slightdust had a huge fight and broke up.
A big bug keeps buzzing around Raingrass and Sunpaw. (neutral effect)
Basaltleopard offers to groom a hard-to-reach place for Goldenblink, who thanks him earnestly. (high positive effect)
Slateflood and Buggs argued about something trivial and neither of them apologized. (low negative effect)
Slateflood thinks that Basaltleopard looks nice today. (low positive effect)
Time has taken its toll and Slightdust has noticed themself slowing down. They have worked timelessly for many moons, but it is time for them to retire.
Basaltleopard gets a bug off of Slightdust's pelt and takes it out of camp. (low positive effect)
Slightdust thinks that Vulturethorn spread a rumor about them. (medium negative effect)
Sunpaw finds a bit of fluff that smells like Ferretslither and adds it to his nest. (low positive effect)
Serpentgleam has survived yellowcough.
Both Serpentgleam and Yellowfang enthusiastically congratulate another Clanmate on something. (high positive effect)
Vulturethorn and Slateflood accidentally startle one another. (neutral effect)
Poemscreech notices one of her friends talking to Emeraldcall. (low negative effect)
When a Clanmate passes by holding stinking herbs, both Poemscreech and Bronzecrag gag. (neutral effect)
